    • Method Detail

      • compress

        public int compress(String filePath)
        HuffmanCompress compress Reads all bytes for the input file, calculates the occurrence of bytes/chars to a table. Builds the Huffman tree out of the occurrences into a MinHeap. Create the encoding table for compressing the file. Convert the tree to a binary string, write the original file size to the first 4 bytes and after that the tree. Encode data and write it.
        Parameters:
        filePath - Path to file to compress
        Returns:
        size of file to be compressed, for performance testing

      • createEncodingTable

        public void createEncodingTable(String[] table,
                                HuffNode node,
                                String code)
        Create encoding table for each byte/char recursively starting at root of tree Once you reach a leaf, save the Character into String table and give it the code generated in the travelsal.
        Parameters:
        table - Encoding table for characters
        node - Node to traverse
        code - Binary string code for nodes created recursively
